: The CBI has taken over investigation of a case relating to Pollution Control Board officials allegedly submitting fake documents in a bribe case at the Thrissur Vigilance Court.The FIR against environmental engineer A.K. Surendran, assistant engineers Sindhu Radhakrishnan, V.A. Suseela Nair, K.S. Vinay and Bindhu Vinod was filed before the Ernakulam Chief Judicial Magistrate Court.Surendran allegedly demanded a bribe of Rs.15 lakh from a granite quarry owner. He and his colleagues allegedly submitted fake documents in the court. â€” Staff Reporter